The crop has come as a relief to large-scale farmers whose harvest from barley and wheat has been declining.Its distinctive yellow flowers now dot many farms across the country, with wheat, barley and maize farmers growing the oil plant to boost soil nutrients and earn good money in the process Canola can be planted as a main crop. However, it is recommended as a rotational crop where one grows wheat, canola, beans and barley –  in that orderFarmers can grow wheat-canola-barley rotation which helps to manage soil erosion better. The crop is also a natural weed suppressant Mau Narok is a scenic agricultural town characterised by rolling hills and large tracts of land.
A cloud of dust reaches unbearable level as one traverses the region, passing Mwisho wa Lami trading centre towards Ole Tipis, about 70km from Narok town.
Until recently, the expansive farms of the region hosted maize, potatoes, barley and wheat exclusively but winds of change are sweeping across the agriculturally rich region as farmers seek better returns.



