Planting
Canola does well in same weather conditions that favour maize, barley and wheat, but is well-suited for soils that do not crack.An acre requires 4 kilos of seeds and the plant can be planted manually, but use of a planter is recommended.The seeds are planted from a half to three quarters inches in the soil. They should not be planted any deeper than one inch because they will not germinate. They should be spaced six to nine inches apart.



